-417317509.text: "Therefore, specific CDK7 inhibition revealed the following : a crucial but partly indirect CDK7 involvement in phosphorylation and activation of CDK4 and CDK6; existence of CDK4 activating kinase (s) other than CDK7; and novel CDK7 dependent positive feedbacks mediated by p21 phosphorylation by CDK4 and CDK2 to sustain CDK4 activation, pRb inactivation, and restriction point passage."
